Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
This 3.47 acre parcel represents a unique opportunity to position your hotel or development in the state’s busiest tourist destination. This highly visible parcel is strategically located one block from the Wisconsin Dells Parkway at the Highway 12 and I-90/94 exit. Surrounded by such large resorts as the 435-room Great Wolf Lodge and the 756-room Kalihari Resort, and across from Outlets at the Dells, which draw more than three million visitors each year.
To encourage development of new national francise hotel properties, the Village of Lake Delton will provide an incentive of up to 15% of the project cost to qualified applicants for hotels built with at least 100 rooms, esesentially offsetting the cost of the land.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Prime Wisconsin Dells Hotel Development Site

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Access: Two curb cuts on Wisconsin Dells Parkway plus access out the back of the parcel.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: The tourism destination of Wisconsin Dells is primarily comprised of the City of Wisconsin Dells and the Village of Lake Delton. Its roots as a tourism community date back more than 150 years when the first visitors came for scenic tours of the Wisconsin River with towering sandstone cliffs hugging its shores. Today, Wisconsin Dells is widely recognized as “The Waterpark Capital of the World,” with 4+ million visitors each year. The area has over 8,000 hotel rooms and 19 campgrounds with nearly 3,200 campsites.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: This 8+ acre parcel along the Wisconsin Dells Parkway represents a unique opportunity to position your business or development next to some of the busiest tourist destinations in the area. The parcel is  strategically located next to Mt. Olympus Water & Theme Park Resort and The Original Wisconsin Ducks, two of the most popular area attractions, highly traveled with 10,400 vehicles per day. The parcel has front and back access points off of the Parkway, which allows for convenient circulation and safe exiting, utilizing County Road A.
